Document: CSGMesh3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_csgmesh3d.rst  
Summary: Properties for configuring the material and mesh used by a CSGMesh3D node.  

Material (Material): The material used in drawing the CSG shape. Setter: set_material(value: Material). Getter: get_material().  

Mesh (Mesh): The mesh resource to use as a CSG shape. Setter: set_mesh(value: Mesh). Getter: get_mesh(). Note: PlaneMesh, PointMesh, QuadMesh, and RibbonTrailMesh are excluded from the type hint as they are non-manifold and incompatible with CSG. Note: When using ArrayMesh, only ARRAY_VERTEX and ARRAY_TEX_UV attributes are used. ARRAY_NORMAL is only used for determining flat shading faces. By default, vertex normals are ignored and recalculated for smooth shading. For flat shading, ensure all face vertex normals are approximately equal.